& [SLMProviderSetConfigurationContract] is the contract for local provider-set configuration
  + [contract_uuid] is 9cadb933-93d8-4c28-b998-cd5cb1401f53
  + [slice_id] is SLM-56
  + [depends_on] is SLM_LLM_Provider_Adapter_Contract, SLM_LM_Studio_Sidecar_Adapter_Contract, SLM_Ollama_Sidecar_Adapter_Skeleton_Contract
  + [status] is verified_wsl

  & [Purpose] is to declare available lower providers without changing semantic graph authority
    = must: preserve stable provider identities
    = must: declare adapter kind, model id, prompt contract, adapter version, and capabilities
    = must: allow mock, LM Studio, Ollama, and future hosted providers
    = must: validate that non-mock providers name a prompt contract
    = must: load configuration without starting a network call
    - never: let provider configuration create graph objects or semantic glyphs

  & [CapabilitySet] is the v0 provider capability vocabulary
